# CORE DIRECTIVE: LOCAL KNOWLEDGE GRAPH
You have access to a custom, local codebase Knowledge Graph API running on http://localhost:3579. 
Before making large refactors, answering architectural questions, or trying to find where specific logic lives, you MUST query this API using `curl` to gain context instead of reading files line-by-line.

# HOW TO USE YOUR TOOLS
1. To see the available tools, run: `curl -s http://localhost:3579/mcp/manifest`
2. To use a tool, make a POST request. Example:
   `curl -X POST http://localhost:3579/mcp -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"tool":"search_intent","params":{"query":"API keys"}}'`

Treat this Knowledge Graph as your primary search engine for this workspace.